This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of computer science that deal with data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The use of probabilistic partitions may also make the paper relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
